\begin_layout Section
Occupancy Matrix
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Occupancy Matrix is a quick glance view of room occupancy.
 The date select and range controls are on top.
 The room lanes show a visual histogram of rooms vs dates.
 Clicking on a room lane wil retrieve basic guest informaton and reservation
 information and a link to additional information and full guest profile
 will display.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Date Select and Range
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The date axis has 3 controls:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The calendar select will adust the date origin of the horizontal date axis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Clicking on any of the dates will push the origin to (day - 4) of the selected
 date.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The slider will adjust the number of days represented up to 30 days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Room Lanes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Room lanes are color coded for easier identification.
 The meaning and variety are all customizable.
 Room status can be realized with just a glance and historical room states
 can be accesed and visualized as well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Reservation Viewer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename img/image309.png
	width 10cm

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Clicking on a room marked in the room lane will display a condensed room
 information block.
 This way one can click through many selections quickly, once desired reservatio
n has been located, selecting the Reservation link navigates to a full reservati
on and guest profile.
\end_layout

